# 🧰 Kubernetes Debugging + Exec Cheat Sheet

```bash
NS=job-scheduler
```

---

## 🐞 1. Core Debugging Commands (FIRST THINGS TO RUN)

### Check pod status

```bash
kubectl get pods -n $NS -o wide
```

### Find failing pods fast

```bash
kubectl get pods -n $NS | egrep "CrashLoopBackOff|Error|Pending"
```

### Describe pod (events + reasons)

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n $NS
```

### Check recent events (sorted)

```bash
kubectl get events -n $NS --sort-by=.lastTimestamp
```

---

## 🔑 2. kubectl exec Cheat Sheet

### Exec into a pod (bash)

```bash
kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -n $NS -- /bin/bash
```

### If bash not available

```bash
kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -n $NS -- /bin/sh
```

### Exec into a deployment

```bash
kubectl exec -it deployment/job-service -n $NS -- /bin/bash
```

### Exec into specific container

```bash
kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -c <container-name> -n $NS -- /bin/bash
```

---

## 🧪 3. In-Pod Debugging Essentials

### Environment variables

```bash
printenv
```

### DNS check

```bash
nslookup kafka
nslookup postgres
nslookup mongo
```

### Connectivity test

```bash
curl http://api-gateway:8080/actuator/health
```

### Check open ports

```bash
netstat -tulpn
```

---

## 🧵 4. Kafka Deep Debugging 🔥

### Kafka pod logs

```bash
kubectl logs -l app=kafka -n $NS
```

### Follow Kafka logs

```bash
kubectl logs -f deployment/kafka -n $NS
```

### Exec into Kafka pod

```bash
kubectl exec -it kafka-0 -n $NS -- /bin/bash
```

### Check Kafka broker status

```bash
ps aux | grep kafka
```

### List topics

```bash
kafka-topics.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --list
```

### Describe topic

```bash
kafka-topics.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --describe --topic <topic>
```

### Consume messages

```bash
kafka-console-consumer.sh \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --topic <topic> \
  --from-beginning
```

### Produce test message

```bash
kafka-console-producer.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic <topic>
```

🚨 **Common Kafka Errors**

| Error                   | Meaning                 |
| ----------------------- | ----------------------- |
| `LEADER_NOT_AVAILABLE`  | Broker not ready        |
| `Connection refused`    | Service / port mismatch |
| `NotLeaderForPartition` | Broker restart needed   |

---

## 🍃 5. MongoDB Deep Debugging

### Mongo pod logs

```bash
kubectl logs -l app=mongodb -n $NS
```

### Exec into Mongo pod

```bash
kubectl exec -it mongo-0 -n $NS -- /bin/bash
```

### Connect to Mongo shell

```bash
mongosh
```

### Check databases

```js
show dbs
```

### Check collections

```js
use jobdb
show collections
```

### Find slow queries

```js
db.currentOp()
```

### Check replica status (if enabled)

```js
rs.status()
```

🚨 **Common Mongo Issues**

| Symptom            | Cause                |
| ------------------ | -------------------- |
| Connection timeout | Service name wrong   |
| `Unauthorized`     | Wrong credentials    |
| CrashLoop          | PVC permission issue |

---

## 🐘 6. Postgres Deep Debugging

### Postgres logs

```bash
kubectl logs -l app=postgres -n $NS
```

### Exec into Postgres pod

```bash
kubectl exec -it postgres-0 -n $NS -- /bin/bash
```

### Connect to Postgres

```bash
psql -U postgres
```

### List databases

```sql
\l
```

### Switch DB

```sql
\c jobdb
```

### List tables

```sql
\dt
```

### Active connections

```sql
SELECT pid, usename, state, query FROM pg_stat_activity;
```

### Lock issues

```sql
SELECT * FROM pg_locks;
```

🚨 **Common Postgres Errors**

| Error                            | Fix                      |
| -------------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| `password authentication failed` | Secret mismatch          |
| `too many connections`           | Increase max_connections |
| CrashLoop                        | Volume permission issue  |

---

