KEYS *
```

---

## 🔍 8. Network & DNS Debugging

### DNS resolution inside cluster

```bash
kubectl run dns-test --rm -it \
  --image=busybox \
  -n $NS -- nslookup kafka
```

### Service endpoints

```bash
kubectl get endpoints -n $NS
```

---

## 🚑 9. Emergency Debug Patterns

### Pod stuck in Pending

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod> -n $NS
```

### PVC issues

```bash
kubectl get pvc -n $NS
kubectl describe pvc <pvc-name> -n $NS
```

### Node issues

```bash
kubectl get nodes
kubectl describe node <node>
```

---

## ⭐ 10. Golden Debug Workflow

```bash
kubectl get pods -n $NS
kubectl describe pod <pod>
kubectl logs <pod>
kubectl logs <pod> --previous
kubectl exec -it <pod> -- /bin/bash
```

---

## 🧠 Pro Production Tips

✔ Always check **events first**
✔ Use **--previous** for crash debugging
✔ DB issues → logs + exec + PVC
✔ Kafka issues → broker logs + topic state
✔ Never debug blind—**describe → logs → exec**

